HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 159
BY REPRESENTATIVE MILLER
SPECIAL DAY/WEEK/MONTH: Designates April 15, 2026, as Louisiana Occupational
Therapy Association Day at the state capitol
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To designate Wednesday, April 15, 2026, as Louisiana Occupational Therapy Association
3 Day at the state capitol.
4 WHEREAS, Louisiana is home to over three thousand licensed occupational
5 therapists and occupational therapy assistants; and
6 WHEREAS, the month of April is recognized nationally as Occupational Therapy
7 Month; and
8 WHEREAS, the Louisiana Occupational Therapy Association advocates for progress
9 and innovation in the occupational therapy profession, promotes high standards of clinical
10 competency, and facilitates statewide relationships with the occupational therapy
11 community; and
12 WHEREAS, occupational therapists use a holistic approach to assist people and help
13 them participate in both necessary and leisurely activities; and
14 WHEREAS, occupational therapy provides numerous benefits to its patients,
15 including a reduction of fall risks and nursing home admissions, lowered readmission rates
16 to hospitals, lowered rates of depression, and improved quality of life for people with
17 chronic disease; and
18 WHEREAS, occupational therapists develop and implement fit for duty and injury
19 prevention programs in the industrial setting, which keep employees healthy and employers
20 financially competitive; and
